id: pm-r9ei
title: Fix Grafana RabbitMQ queue panel metric selector mismatch
description: "Telemetry overview dashboard queue panels query rabbitmq_queue_messages{queue=\"pm.telemetry.events\"} and rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked{queue=\"pm.telemetry.events\"}, but current Prometheus series on the remote stack have no queue label, so the panel query returns empty data despite non-zero queue depth."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[6]: external-audit,grafana,observability,pm-cli,prometheus,telemetry
created_at: "2026-04-26T09:56:16.564Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-03T13:54:23.216Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: Grafana queue panels render live queue depth and unacked values in production by aligning panel queries with actual metric labels (or by exposing the queue label in exporter config).
parent: pm-lnq3
resolution: Grafana queue panel PromQL now uses job-scoped aggregates that match the RabbitMQ exporter label model on this stack.
expected_result: Queue depth and unacked panels evaluate successfully without relying on absent queue labels.
actual_result: "Dashboard expressions now use sum(rabbitmq_queue_messages{job=\"rabbitmq\"}) and sum(rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked{job=\"rabbitmq\"}); Prometheus returns non-empty vectors and Grafana remains healthy."
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-lnq3,parent,"2026-04-26T09:56:16.564Z",codex-agent,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-03T13:33:58.503Z",codex-audit,"Sanitized current comments: Grafana/RabbitMQ selector evidence is preserved in resolution/notes/learnings and prior comments were cleared from the current item because one contained a private remote operations path. History-stream redaction requires a dedicated audited pm command to preserve replay integrity."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:29:32.022Z",codex-agent,"Fix strategy gate: inspect live Grafana dashboard JSON first, then patch query expressions to match actual exported RabbitMQ series labels unless exporter-level label restoration is clearly lower-risk."
  "2026-04-27T19:39:00.791Z",codex-agent,"Root cause is label-model mismatch: RabbitMQ exporter emits queue gauges with instance/job labels in this profile, not queue label selectors, so panel queries should aggregate over job-scoped series."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:39:04.640Z",codex-agent,"For host-level diagnostics on this stack, use Prometheus published port 19090 (not container-internal 9090) to avoid false-negative query conclusions during dashboard triage."
files[1]{path,scope,note}:
  scripts/prod/telemetry/2026-04-27-pm-cli-telemetry-overview.json,project,local snapshot of patched Grafana dashboard JSON
